Thebes was always one of the capital cities of Greece: Isoc. paneg. But the number of its citizens exceeded not those of Rhodes.
Diod Sic. lib. 15 and 17. Phliasia is said to be a small city by Xenophon;
Hist. Graec. lib. 7. yet we find, that it contain'd 6000 citizens. Id. lib. 7. I pretend not to reconcile these two facts.

THE antient Helvetia was 240 miles in length, and 180 in breadth, according to Caesar;
De bello Gallico, lib. 1. yet con
tain'd only 360,000 inhabitants. The canton of Berne alone, has, at present, as many people.
